---
id: org.dxos.plugin.ideogram
name: IdeogramPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

A **headless** Composer plugin that makes [ideogram.ai](https://ideogram.ai)
available as an image-generation provider. It has no React/UI surfaces. It
contributes two things:

1. A **Connector** entry (`source: "ideogram.ai"`) with an API-key
   credential form, so the user connects Ideogram through the generic
   `plugin-connector` UI. On submit the key is stored as an `AccessToken`
   (source `ideogram.ai`) plus a `Connection` in ECHO.
2. An **`ImageGenerationService`** implementation (the abstraction owned by
   `plugin-studio`) whose `generate()` calls the Ideogram HTTP API and
   maps the response to `GeneratedImageData[]`.

The credential set up by the Connector is resolved back at generation time
by `plugin-studio`'s `generateImage` operation through
`CredentialsService`, keyed by the provider's `source`. This plugin never
reads the prompt UI and `plugin-studio` never reads Ideogram
credentials — the Connector + `CredentialsService` are the seam.

## Extensions

| Term   | URI                     |
| ------ | ----------------------- |
| `type` | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0` |
| `feat` | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0` |
| `test` | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0` |

## Connector

```mdl
feat IdeogramConnector
  desc: >
    Contributes a ConnectorEntry via Capability.contributes(Connector,
    [entry]) on the SetupConnectors activation event (mirrors
    plugin-ibkr's non-OAuth credentialForm connector).
  id: org.dxos.plugin.ideogram.connector
  source: ideogram.ai
  label: Ideogram
  credentialForm:
    schema: IdeogramTokenForm { token: string }   # the API key
    onSubmit: >
      Trim the token; if empty, throw. Build
      Obj.make(AccessToken, { source: "ideogram.ai", token }) and
      Obj.make(Connection, { name: "Ideogram", connectorId: <id>,
      accessToken: Ref.make(accessToken) }); return
      { kind: "complete", accessToken, connection }.
```

## Provider

```mdl
feat IdeogramImageGenerationService
  desc: >
    Contributes an ImageGenerationService via
    Capability.contributes(StudioCapabilities.ImageGenerationService,
    [service]) on Startup. Provider-agnostic contract from
    @dxos/plugin-studio/types.
  id: ideogram
  label: Ideogram
  source: ideogram.ai
  generate:
    endpoint: POST https://api.ideogram.ai/generate
    auth: header "Api-Key: <token>"        # from options.apiKey (Redacted)
    request:
      # { image_request: { prompt, aspect_ratio?, model?, magic_prompt_option?,
      #   negative_prompt?, seed?, style_type?, num_images? } }
      prompt: request.prompt
      aspect_ratio?: request.aspectRatio
      model?: request.model                 # default V_2
      negative_prompt?: request.negativePrompt
      seed?: request.seed
      style_type?: request.styleType
      num_images?: request.count             # default 1
    response:
      # { created, request_id?, data: [{ url, prompt, resolution, seed,
      #   is_image_safe, style_type? }] }
      map: >
        data[] → GeneratedImageData {
          url, prompt, model: request.model ?? "V_2", resolution, seed,
          styleType: style_type, isImageSafe: is_image_safe,
          metadata: { requestId, created }
        }
    errors:
      - missing apiKey → throw MissingCredential.
      - non-2xx → throw GenerationError with status + body.
    notes:
      - Provider image URLs are ephemeral (documented by Ideogram).
      - api.ideogram.ai does not permit browser CORS, so the request is routed
        through the DXOS edge CORS proxy (`proxyFetchLegacy` from
        `@dxos/edge-client`); the `Api-Key` header passes through unchanged.
```

## File layout (mirrors plugin-osrm)

```text
packages/plugins/plugin-ideogram/
  PLUGIN.mdl                         # this file
  README.md
  package.json                       # "private": true
  moon.yml                           # --entryPoint per export subpath; platform=neutral
  src/
    index.ts                         # exports meta + IdeogramPlugin
    meta.ts                          # Plugin.getMetaFromConfig (id org.dxos.plugin.ideogram)
    plugin.ts                        # Plugin.lazy
    IdeogramPlugin.tsx               # Plugin.define(meta).pipe(addModule Connector on SetupConnectors, addModule Provider on Startup, Plugin.make)
    dx.config.ts
    capabilities/
      index.ts                       # Capability.lazy(Connector, ImageGenerationService)
      connector.ts                   # Capability.contributes(Connector, [entry])
      image-generation-service.ts    # Capability.contributes(StudioCapabilities.ImageGenerationService, [service])
    services/
      index.ts
      IdeogramClient.ts              # generate(request, { apiKey }) → GeneratedImageData[]
      ideogram-mapping.ts            # response → GeneratedImageData[]
      ideogram-mapping.test.ts       # fixture-based unit test
```

## Dependencies

- `@dxos/plugin-studio` (workspace:\*) — `/types` subpath for the
  `ImageGenerationService` capability key + request/result schemas.
- `@dxos/plugin-connector` (workspace:\*) — `Connector` capability key +
  `Connection` type; `@dxos/types` for `AccessToken`.
- `@dxos/app-framework`, `@dxos/app-toolkit`, `@dxos/echo`, `effect`.
- No `react` / `@dxos/react-ui*`.

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Connector builds AccessToken + Connection
  given: the Ideogram ConnectorEntry
  when: credentialForm.onSubmit runs with { token: "sk-…" }
  then:
    - returns kind "complete"
    - accessToken.source === "ideogram.ai" and accessToken.token === "sk-…"
    - connection.connectorId === the entry id and references the accessToken
```

```mdl
test T-2: Empty token rejected
  given: the Ideogram ConnectorEntry
  when: credentialForm.onSubmit runs with { token: "  " }
  then: it throws (no AccessToken / Connection created)
```

```mdl
test T-3: Response mapping (mocked fetch)
  given: a mocked /generate response with 2 data entries
  when: IdeogramClient.generate({ prompt }, { apiKey }) runs
  then:
    - 2 GeneratedImageData returned, url/seed/resolution/isImageSafe mapped
    - the request body nests fields under image_request and sends header Api-Key
```

```mdl
test T-4: Missing key
  given: IdeogramClient.generate called with no apiKey
  then: it throws MissingCredential (no network call)
```

## Out of scope (v1)

- OAuth (Ideogram uses a static API key).
- Edit / upscale / remix / describe endpoints; only `/generate`.
- Multi-account and per-artifact provider configuration.
- A server-side (edge function) transport that keeps the API key off the client
  entirely; v1 resolves the key client-side and proxies the call.
